  "plan": "## KNNXValidation GenePattern Module — Implementation Plan\n\n### 1. Overview\nKNNXValidation is a GenePattern module that KNN classification with Leave-One-Out Cross-Validation\n\n### 2. Parameters\nThe module exposes 10 parameters:\n- Required: data.filename, class.filename, num.features, feature.selection.statistic, num.neighbors, weighting.type, distance.measure, pred.results.file, feature.summary.file\n- Optional: min.std\n\n### 3. Command Line\n```\n<java> <java_flags> -cp <libdir>gp-modules.jar<path.separator><libdir>knnxval.jar org.genepattern.modules.knnxval.KNNXValidation -t<data.filename> -c<class.filename> -o<pred.results.file> -n<num.features> -f<feature.summary.file> -k<num.neighbors> -w<weighting.type> -d<distance.measure> -S<feature.selection.statistic> -M<min.std>\n```\n\n### 4. Docker Image\nDocker image: \n\n### 5. Validation Strategy\n- Validate all required parameters are provided\n- Validate file formats match expected extensions\n- Check parameter value ranges where applicable\n\n### 6. Implementation Roadmap\nPhase 1: Wrapper script implementation\nPhase 2: Docker container setup\nPhase 3: Parameter validation and error handling\nPhase 4: Testing and documentation",
